results.name: Let c=sum_{k>=0} 1/2^(k!). Sequence gives values of terms not congruent to 5 in the continued fraction for c.
comment: Appears to contain only 1,2,3 or 4; seems to be a pseudo-periodic sequence.
example: The continued fraction for c is shown in A076157. "Big terms" are all congruent to 5.
results.author: _Benoit Cloitre_, Nov 02 2002
